top_5_data <- tuition_cost %>% 
  filter(!is.na(state)) %>%

  • âfrequencyâ containing the corresponding word frequencies.

Task 5 (5 points)

Write a function in R to find the longest word in a given sentence. Example: find_longest_word("R is a great language for data analysis") should return c("analysis", "language").

find_longest_word <- function(sentence){
  
  words <- unlist(strsplit(sentence, " "))
  
  max_length <- max(nchar(words))
  
  words[ max_length == nchar(words)]
  
  
}


find_longest_word("R is a great language for data analysis")
[1] "language" "analysis"

Task 8 (5 points)

Using the carsDF dataframe, create a scatter plot in ggplot2 with:

  • x-axis: price

  • y-axis: powerPS

Ensure the x-axis scale is appropriate. Add facets by fuelType (only for benzin, diesel, lpg). Add a chart title and a horizontal line. Ensure the chart looks nice by applying a theme and adjusting the space and scales in facets.

 carsDF %>% filter(fuelType=="benzin" | fuelType =="lpg" | fuelType =="diesel") %>%
 ggplot(aes(x = price, y = powerPS)) +
  geom_jitter(size = 0.5,color ="blue") +
   scale_x_continuous(breaks = seq(0,80000,by = 40000))+
  facet_wrap(~fuelType) +
   geom_hline(yintercept = 350, linetype = "dashed",color ="red")+
   labs(
     title = "The price - powerPS graphic",
     x = "Price",
     y= "powerPS"
   )+theme_minimal()

Task 9 (3 points)

Calculate the difference in seconds between the following two dates:

x <- "11th april 2012 14:21:24"
y <- "May 24th 2024 11:59:59"

datex <-as.POSIXct(x , format="%dth %b %Y %H:%M:%S")
datex
[1] "2012-04-11 14:21:24 CEST"
datey <- as.POSIXct(y , format = "%b %dth %Y %H:%M:%S")
datey
[1] "2024-05-24 11:59:59 CEST"
time_difference <-difftime(datey,datex,units = "secs")

paste("The time difference is ",time_difference)
[1] "The time difference is  382397915"
